The numbers are placed on a clockwise square‑spiral with  

* 1 at \((0,0)\)  
* 2 at \((1,0)\)  

and the rule that the numbers increase as we go right, up, left, down, …  

---

### 1.  Locate 2026  

The largest square ≤ 2026 is \(45^{2}=2025\).  
Thus 2026 is the first element of the next “ring”, whose radius is  

\[
k=23 \qquad\bigl((2k+1)^2=47^2=2209\bigr).
\]

The first element of ring \(k\) is at  

\[
(x,y)=\bigl(k,\,-(k-1)\bigr)=(23,-22).
\]

Hence 2026 occupies \((23,-22)\).

---

### 2.  Number at any coordinate  

For a point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
k=\max(|x|,|y|),\qquad t=(2k+1)^2 .
\]

Depending on which side of the square the point lies on, the number is

\[
\begin{cases}
y=k   &\Rightarrow n=t-(k-x) \\[2pt]
x=-k  &\Rightarrow n=t-2k-(k-y) \\[2pt]
y=-k  &\Rightarrow n=t-4k-(x+k) \\[2pt]
x=k   &\Rightarrow n=t-6k-(y+k) .
\end{cases}
\]

(These formulas give the correct values for the sample layout.)

---

### 3.  The eight neighbours of \((23,-22)\)

| neighbour (dx,dy) | coordinate \((x,y)\) | \(k\) | side | \(n\) |
|-------------------|----------------------|------|------|-------|
| (‑1,‑1) | (22,‑23) | 23 | top (\(y=-k\)) | \(2209-4·23-(22+23)=2072\) |
| (0,‑1)  | (23,‑23) | 23 | top | \(2209-4·23-(23+23)=2071\) |
| (1,‑1)  | (24,‑23) | 24 | right (\(x=k\)) | \(2401-6·24-(-23+24)=2256\) |
| (‑1,0)  | (22,‑22) | 22 | right | \(2025-6·22-(-22+22)=1893\) |
| (1,0)   | (24,‑22) | 24 | right | \(2401-6·24-(-22+24)=2255\) |
| (‑1,1)  | (22,‑21) | 22 | right | \(2025-6·22-(-21+22)=1892\) |
| (0,1)   | (23,‑21) | 23 | right | \(2209-6·23-(-21+23)=2069\) |
| (1,1)   | (24,‑21) | 24 | right | \(2401-6·24-(-21+24)=2254\) |

---

### 4.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
S&=2072+2071+2256+1893+2255+1892+2069+2254\\
 &=16762 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16762}
\]
